<title type="html"><![CDATA[9/7 The Science of Procrastination / Why do you always feel tired? (Host:Way)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=74&amp;p=78#p78"><![CDATA[
<span style="font-weight: bold">9/7 Article  Host: Way</span><br /><br />Hi royal member, I didn’t print out the content of these two articles because I hope participants can practice English listening by watching/listening the attached youtube video website. There are many items you can adjust in the settings including languish type, speaking speed, subtitle etc. to make you better comprehend it and be able to repeat listening until you feel comfortable .Let’s join this English learning journey together and express your opinion during Thursday gathering. Thanks for your participation.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session 1 - The Science of Procrastination - And How To Manage It</span><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1nBwfZZvjKo" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1nBwfZZvjKo</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion</span><br />1. Are you a person who like to complete your mission by procrastination? What reasons cause you not to be on track all the time?<br />2. Do you think removing temptations around you can prevent procrastination? What do you think procrastination can be avoided?<br />3. What do you think “No pressure, no progress”? Decent pressure can make people move forward than no pressure at all?<br />4. Please share your tips with your members- how to manage procrastination? <br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session 2 - Why do you always feel tired?</span><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nn42RC1zT_A" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nn42RC1zT_A</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion</span><br />1. What’s your sleep quality? Do you sleep well every night?<br />2. If not, what factors make your sleep be in bad shape?<br />3. Dose caffeine help you to be energetic? Any other stuff makes you wake up?  <br />4. Any suggestion do you have to share with your members to improve sleep quality?<br />5. Are you a night owl? Do you like to be a night owl or forced to be?<br />6. How do you overcome physical or emotional fatigue and keep energetic in most time?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=49">josh</a> — Tue Sep 05, 2017 10:34 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
